<p>â€‹How can I iterate over the compound literal array so that I can print <code>book_id</code> and <code>value</code>?</p>  <pre><code>#include &lt;stdio.h&gt; #include &lt;string.h&gt;  typedef struct {     int book_id;     char value; } BookCode;  typedef struct {     BookCode *codes; } Books;  int main() {     Books MyBooks[] = {          (BookCode[]){ {1, 'a'},{2, 'b'} },         (BookCode[]){ {1, 'd'},{2, 'c'}, {3, 'f'} },     };        int i,j;     int n1 = sizeof(MyBooks)/sizeof(MyBooks[0]);     for(i = 0; i &lt; n1; i++){         printf("%d\n", i);          // how to iterate over compound literal array?     }        return 0; } </code></pre>